.TH "spum_hash_pad_len" 9 "spum_hash_pad_len" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
spum_hash_pad_len \- Calculate the length of hash padding required to extend data to a full block size.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "u16" spum_hash_pad_len
.BI "(enum hash_alg hash_alg "  ","
.BI "enum hash_mode hash_mode "  ","
.BI "u32 chunksize "  ","
.BI "u16 hash_block_size "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "hash_alg" 12
hash algorithm
.IP "hash_mode" 12
hash mode
.IP "chunksize" 12
length of data, in bytes
.IP "hash_block_size" 12
size of a block of data for hash algorithm
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Reserve space for 1 byte (0x80) start of pad and the total length as u64
.SH "RETURN"
length of hash pad in bytes
